IModuleInterface for all modules (things that are displayed in a Player).
Functions and Properties
bufferIndication that module will soon need to display itself.
bufferedSee whether or not a time range is loaded and ready for display.
unbufferMarks assets for partial unloading If the module has loaded external media through the LoadManager it should unbuffer it during this call.
unloadMarks assets for complete unloading
runningAsPreviewCalled if instance is icon of Browser or Timeline preview
animatingCalled if instance is icon of Browser or Timeline preview and it’s selected
getFrameCurrent clip time for module (read/write).
playingChanges playback state (write only).
volumeChanges playback volume (write only).
clipSets associated Clip (write only).

Parameters

firstint containing first frame
lastint containing last frame
muteBoolean object indicating whether or not sound is needed.
rebufferBoolean object indicating whether or not this module playing at both the start and end of mash.

function set clip(iClip: IClip):void

Sets associated Clip (write only).  The pointer sent can be cast to an IClip or Clip pointer if desired.  IPropertied is used here to minimize compile size.
